<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-09T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 185.119/39a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                            </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-09T12:00:00+00:00">January 9, 1919—12
                            noon</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>211. [From Lansing.] The Commission would be glad to receive from the
                        Department by mail as soon as possible a statement of the claims of American
                        Citizens against Germany. Lansing.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>